from google.colab import files
import librosa
import librosa.display
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload the audio file to Google Colab
uploaded = files.upload()

# Choose the uploaded audio file
for filename in uploaded.keys():
    audio_path = filename

librosa.display.specshow(spec, y_axis='log', x_axis='time', sr=sample_rate)
plt.colorbar(format='%+2.0f dB')
plt.title('Spectrogram of the Uploaded Audio File')

In [26]:
# Load the audio file
audio_file = audio_path
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from pydub import AudioSegment
from pyAudioAnalysis import audioBasicIO, audioSegmentation


# Read the audio file and extract the sampling rate
sampling_rate, audio_data = audioBasicIO.read_audio_file(audio_file)

# Perform segmentation with specified parameters
frame_size = 0.05  # 50ms
frame_step = 0.025  # 25ms
segments = audioSegmentation.silence_removal(audio_data, sampling_rate, frame_size, frame_step)

# Plot the segments
for seg in segments:
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 2))
    plt.plot(np.arange(len(seg)) * frame_step, seg)
    plt.title('Segment')
    plt.show()

from pydub import AudioSegment
import speech_recognition as sr
from google.colab import files

if 'wav' not in audio_path:
  # Convert MP3 to WAV
  audio = AudioSegment.from_mp3(audio_path)
  audio_path = "audio.wav"
  audio.export(audio_path, format="wav")

# Load the WAV file
r = sr.Recognizer()
with sr.AudioFile(audio_path) as source:
    audio_data = r.record(source)

# Convert audio to text
try:
    text = r.recognize_google(audio_data)
    print("Transcription: " + text)
except sr.UnknownValueError:
    print("Google Speech Recognition could not understand the audio.")
except sr.RequestError as e:
    print(f"Could not request results from Google Speech Recognition service; {e}")
